Based off of the studio recorded version (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z3UCVQIjAJ8). Important: In the bridge section, count 6 beats per chord instead of 4 to give it the slowed down feel. Continue with 4 beats in the outro.
Four chords song but the movement of the words change thats all.

From the record version: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jCSvOtUaI8s. In the record, a lot of the notes being played are only bass notes, so I have added extra notes so that you can hear the chord. The D chord in brackets is only for those who want to play a more simple rhythm (the syncopated rhythm can be difficult to play correctly while singing as it starts on an off beat).
Its accurate, the chords are properly situated and in place.
